title: 820-3330-b no green light
message:
PPBUS is missing
PP3V42_G3H is missing
SMC_BC_ACOK is missing
R7005 near ISL is dead. Should I change R7005 and ISL?

title: 820-3330-b no green light
message: ISL will not work properly with missing R7005. Change the resistor first, verify there are no shorts and then make sure you have proper voltage on pin 2 and 3 of U7000 before replacing, unless of course U7000 is causing a short in which case you should just replace that as well.

title: 820-3330-b no green light
message: Uhm no! R7005 is dead because of a short in U7000. Always change them both. Also check R7021/22/51/52

title: 820-3330-b no green light
message:
Changed R7005 and U7000.
R7021/22/51/52 are fine.

What changed: PP3V42_G3H is present this time. Still no green light, PPBUS or ACOK.
ISL also gets pretty hot.

title: 820-3330-b no green light
message: Check your soldering job, also measure resistance from F7040 to GND and report value....

title: 820-3330-b no green light
message: If ISL gets hot it is either soldered wrong or it was killed.
